SIMPLE: parol
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parol
<hw>Pa*rol"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Parole</er>,
the same word.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A word; an oral utterance.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Oral declaration; word of mouth;
also, a writing not under seal.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parol</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Parol
<hw>Pa*rol"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Given or done by word of mouth;
oral; also, given by a writing not under seal; <as>as, <ex>parol</ex>
evidence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Parol arrest</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>an arrest in
pursuance of a verbal order from a magistrate.</cd> -- <col><b>Parol
contract</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>any contract not of record or
under seal, whether oral or written; a simple contract.</cd>
<rj><au>Chitty. Story.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parole</ent>⟦br⟧
